 'ራሶቹ' to 'ራስ'.\n\n**PROTOCOL 6 (THE GRAMMARIAN):** Each word was assigned a high-level part of speech (Noun or Verb).\n\n**PROTOCOL 7 (THE FILTER):** In strict adherence to this protocol, all single-character words or roots were discarded from the final output. This includes the preposition 'ከ' and the conjunction/particle 'ም', which were identified during splitting but subsequently filtered out due to their single-character length. This decision was made to strictly follow the stated rule, despite 'ከ' and 'ም' being fundamental and meaningful grammatical units in Amharic.\n\n**Scholarly Guesses:** For words like 'ረአብ', 'ረዓምያ', 'ረዓብያ', 'ረዕላያ', 'ረዜማ', 'ሪሳ', 'ሪኦት', 'ሪኮ', 'ሪያን', 'ራሃይታ', 'ራይላ', the classification as 'Proper Noun' is a scholarly guess based on their non-standard Amharic root structure and resemblance to names found in various contexts (e.g., biblical, foreign). For 'ረጫ' and 'ረጭ', the interpretation as related to 'ሩጫ' (running) and 'መሮጥ' (to run) was chosen over 'መረጨት' (to sprinkle) due to contextual plausibility within a typical Amharic corpus.","input_words":["ከረአብም","ከረከመ","ከረዓምያ","ከረዓብያ","ከረዕላያ","ከረዜማ","ከረዱኝ","ከረግረግም","ከረጢተ","ከረጢቱንም","ከረጫ","ከረጭ","ከረፈደብዎ","ከሩጫውም","ከሪሳም","ከሪትማም","ከሪኦት","ከሪኮ","ከሪዛይኔሽን","ከሪያን","ከሪፍት","ከሪፐብሊክ","ከራሃይታ","ከራረሙ","ከራስቅል","ከራስን","ከራሶቹም","ከራቀህ","ከራይላ","ከራይድ"],"batch_number":null,"batch_label":null,"model_version":"gemini-2.5-flash"},{"id":"d6d4a29b-a634-4ff8-abff-4f089a428226","created_at":"2026-03-04T08:17:38.158614+00:00","word":null,"source_file":"rare_words_24/chunk_0656.txt","batch_index":0,"words":[{"pos":"Verb","root":"ከሰነ","word":"ከሰናቸዋል","synonyms":["to accuse","to sue","to charge"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ሰናፊል","word":"ከሰናፊላቸው","synonyms":["seraphim"],"importance":6},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ሰንበር","word":"ከሰንበሮቹ","synonyms":["weed","thorn","bramble"],"importance":6},{"pos":"Noun","root":"ሰንበት","word":"ከሰንበታቴ","synonyms":["Sabbath","Sunday"],"importance":7},{"pos":"Verb","root":"መስከር","word":"ከሰከሩ","synonyms":